<item>
            <title>[WFLY-7265] Adding Elytron ldap-realm through CLI throws IllegalArgumentException</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-7265</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In case when ldap-realm is added through CLI then IllegalArgumentException is thrown in all cases when values for &lt;tt&gt;identity-mapping.user-password-mapper.writable&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;identity-mapping.user-password-mapper.verifiable&lt;/tt&gt; are not set. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to read-attribute operation these attributes (writable and verifiable) should has set default values hence they should not be required by CLI. &lt;/p&gt;

